# APCOM Platform — Cursor Rules & Style Guide

> Every file generated or modified by Cursor will follow the APCOM brand system below.

---

## 1. PROJECT CONTEXT

You are building a web platform for **APCOM**, an Apple Authorised Distributor operating across Central & Eastern Europe (Romania, Bulgaria, Hungary, Czech Republic, Slovakia, Croatia, Serbia, Slovenia, Bosnia & Herzegovina, Montenegro, Kosovo, and Albania). APCOM is part of the Midis Group.

The platform is a **B2B distribution portal** serving authorized resellers and partners. The visual identity must feel **premium, clean, and Apple-adjacent** — professional without being sterile, modern without being trendy.

---

## 2. DESIGN PHILOSOPHY

Follow these principles in every UI decision:

- **Clean & minimal**: Generous whitespace, clear hierarchy, no visual clutter.
- **Apple-adjacent aesthetic**: The brand sits next to Apple products — the UI must feel worthy of that context. Think apple.com editorial quality.
- **Green as the action color**: APCOM's signature green (#5CB85C) is used exclusively for primary CTAs, success states, and key highlights. Never overuse it — it should pop when it appears.
- **Dark contrast blocks**: Use dark backgrounds (#222222) for hero sections, footers, and emphasis blocks to create rhythm.
- **Soft depth**: Rounded corners (8–12px), subtle shadows, smooth hover transitions. No hard edges or flat brutalism.
- **Content-first**: Let data and products breathe. UI serves the content, not the other way around.

---

## 3. COLOR SYSTEM

Use CSS custom properties everywhere. Never hardcode hex values inline — always reference the design tokens below.

### 3.1 CSS Variables

```css
:root {
  /* ── Core Brand ── */
  --apcom-black:        #1A1A1A;
  --apcom-dark:         #222222;
  --apcom-charcoal:     #333333;
  --apcom-slate:        #4A4A4A;

  /* ── Signature Green (primary accent) ── */
  --apcom-green:        #5CB85C;
  --apcom-green-hover:  #4CAE4C;
  --apcom-green-dark:   #3D8B3D;
  --apcom-green-light:  #8ED08E;

  /* ── Blue Accent (links & interactive) ── */
  --apcom-blue:         #2A7DE1;
  --apcom-blue-hover:   #1A6DD1;
  --apcom-blue-light:   #EBF3FD;

  /* ── Neutral Scale ── */
  --apcom-white:        #FFFFFF;
  --apcom-off-white:    #F8F8F8;
  --apcom-light-gray:   #F0F0F0;
  --apcom-mid-gray:     #E0E0E0;
  --apcom-gray:         #999999;
  --apcom-dark-gray:    #666666;

  /* ── Semantic ── */
  --apcom-success:      #5CB85C;
  --apcom-warning:      #F0AD4E;
  --apcom-danger:       #D9534F;
  --apcom-info:         #5BC0DE;

  /* ── Typography ── */
  --font-heading: 'DM Sans', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif;
  --font-body:    'DM Sans', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif;
  --font-mono:    'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', 'Consolas', monospace;

  /* ── Spacing Scale ── */
  --space-xs:   4px;
  --space-sm:   8px;
  --space-md:  16px;
  --space-lg:  24px;
  --space-xl:  32px;
  --space-2xl: 48px;
  --space-3xl: 64px;
  --space-4xl: 96px;

  /* ── Border Radius ── */
  --radius-sm:   4px;
  --radius-md:   8px;
  --radius-lg:  12px;
  --radius-xl:  16px;
  --radius-pill: 999px;

  /* ── Shadows ── */
  --shadow-sm:  0 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
  --shadow-md:  0 4px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  --shadow-lg:  0 8px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
  --shadow-xl:  0 20px 60px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
}
```

### 3.2 Color Usage Rules

| Token                  | When to use                                         |
|------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------|
| `--apcom-black`        | Page headings (h1, h2), navbar logo text             |
| `--apcom-dark`         | Dark section backgrounds, footer background          |
| `--apcom-charcoal`     | Default body text                                    |
| `--apcom-slate`        | Secondary text, nav links, descriptions              |
| `--apcom-green`        | Primary buttons, active nav items, success badges    |
| `--apcom-green-hover`  | Button hover states only                             |
| `--apcom-green-dark`   | Button active/pressed states                         |
| `--apcom-green-light`  | Tag backgrounds, light success backgrounds           |
| `--apcom-blue`         | Text links, secondary interactive elements           |
| `--apcom-blue-hover`   | Link hover states                                    |
| `--apcom-blue-light`   | Info banners, tooltip backgrounds                    |
| `--apcom-off-white`    | Alternating section backgrounds                      |
| `--apcom-light-gray`   | Card borders, dividers, section separators            |
| `--apcom-mid-gray`     | Input borders (default state)                        |
| `--apcom-gray`         | Placeholder text, captions, overlines                |
| `--apcom-dark-gray`    | Card descriptions, meta information                  |

### 3.3 Color DON'Ts

- NEVER use raw hex values — always use CSS variables.
- NEVER use the green for backgrounds of large areas — it's an accent, not a theme color.
- NEVER mix multiple bright accent colors in the same component.
- NEVER use pure black (#000000) — use `--apcom-black` (#1A1A1A) instead.

---

## 4. TYPOGRAPHY

### 4.1 Font Stack

- **Primary font**: `DM Sans` (Google Fonts) for both headings and body.
- **Monospace**: `SF Mono` → `Fira Code` → `Consolas` for code blocks and technical data.
- **Import**: `https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Sans:ital,opsz,wght@0,9..40,300;0,9..40,400;0,9..40,500;0,9..40,600;0,9..40,700;1,9..40,400&display=swap`

### 4.2 Type Scale

| Level       | Size     | Weight | Line Height | Letter Spacing | Usage                        |
|-------------|----------|--------|-------------|----------------|------------------------------|
| H1          | 2.4rem   | 700    | 1.15        | -0.03em        | Page titles, hero headings   |
| H2          | 1.8rem   | 600    | 1.25        | -0.02em        | Section headings             |
| H3          | 1.35rem  | 600    | 1.35        | normal         | Subsection headings          |
| H4          | 1.1rem   | 600    | 1.4         | normal         | Card titles, dialog titles   |
| Body Large  | 1.05rem  | 400    | 1.6         | normal         | Lead paragraphs, intros      |
| Body        | 0.9rem   | 400    | 1.6         | normal         | Default body text            |
| Body Small  | 0.82rem  | 400    | 1.55        | normal         | Descriptions, meta text      |
| Caption     | 0.75rem  | 500    | 1.4         | 0.05em         | Overlines, labels (UPPERCASE)|
| Overline    | 0.7rem   | 600    | 1.4         | 0.15em         | Section labels (UPPERCASE)   |

### 4.3 Typography Rules

- Always use `-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased` on the body.
- Headings use **tight** negative letter-spacing for a premium feel.
- Body text uses `--apcom-charcoal` (#333), NOT black.
- Captions and overlines are always UPPERCASE with letter-spacing.
- Never use font sizes smaller than 0.7rem.

---

## 5. COMPONENT PATTERNS

### 5.1 Buttons

- Primary actions (submit, save, confirm) → green background (`--apcom-green`)
- Secondary/navigation actions → dark or outline variant
- Tertiary/text actions → ghost variant
- Destructive actions → red variant using `--apcom-danger`
- All buttons get `translateY(-1px)` + shadow on hover for micro-lift effect
- Border radius: `--radius-md` (8px)
- Font: 600 weight, 0.85rem

### 5.2 Cards

- Always have a 1px border using `--apcom-light-gray`
- Always use `border-radius: 12px`
- Hover state: lift 3px + large shadow
- Card tags/badges use green light background: `background: rgba(92, 184, 92, 0.1); color: var(--apcom-green);`
- Card body padding: 24px

### 5.3 Form Inputs

- Focus state always uses green border + green glow ring
- Labels: 0.78rem, font-weight 600, `--apcom-charcoal`
- Error state: `--apcom-danger` border + red glow ring
- Never use background colors on inputs — keep them white
- Border: 1.5px solid `--apcom-mid-gray`

### 5.4 Navigation

- White background with subtle bottom border or shadow
- Logo: "apcom" wordmark in `--apcom-black`, with a green dot accent
- Nav links: `--apcom-slate`, 0.82rem, font-weight 500
- Active link: `--apcom-green`, font-weight 600
- CTA button in nav: green, small, pill-shaped

### 5.5 Dark Sections

- Background: `--apcom-dark` (#222222)
- Border radius: 12px
- Padding: 48px 32px
- Text: white, paragraphs #AAAAAA
- Use for: hero CTAs, partner program banners, footer, testimonial blocks

### 5.6 Tables (for data-heavy B2B views)

- Headers: uppercase, 0.72rem, letter-spacing 0.08em, `--apcom-gray`
- Rows: hover background `--apcom-off-white`
- Cell borders: 1px solid `--apcom-light-gray`
- Font size: 0.85rem

### 5.7 Badges & Tags

- Font size: 0.65rem, uppercase, letter-spacing 0.1em
- Padding: 3px 8px
- Border radius: 4px
- Green: `rgba(92, 184, 92, 0.1)` bg, `--apcom-green` text
- Blue: `rgba(42, 125, 225, 0.1)` bg, `--apcom-blue` text
- Red: `rgba(217, 83, 79, 0.1)` bg, `--apcom-danger` text
- Yellow: `rgba(240, 173, 78, 0.1)` bg, `--apcom-warning` text

---

## 6. LAYOUT & SPACING

- **Max content width**: 1200px, centered with auto margins
- **Page padding**: 24px on mobile, 48px on desktop
- **Section spacing**: 96px between major sections
- **Card grids**: `display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 24px;`
- **Always use the spacing scale** — never use arbitrary pixel values

---

## 7. INTERACTION & MOTION

- **Transitions**: Always `0.2s ease` for hover states
- **Hover lift**: Buttons and cards lift with `transform: translateY(-Npx)` + shadow increase
- **Focus rings**: Green glow using `box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(92, 184, 92, 0.15)`
- **Page loads**: Use subtle fade-in (`opacity 0→1, translateY 8px→0`) for content sections
- **No jarring animations** — everything should feel smooth and intentional

---

## 8. SHADCN/UI THEME MAPPING

This project uses shadcn/ui with Tailwind CSS v4. The theme is configured via CSS variables in `app/globals.css`.

Light mode (`:root`) maps APCOM brand colors to shadcn variables:
- `--primary` → APCOM green (#5CB85C)
- `--foreground` → APCOM charcoal (#333333)
- `--background` → white (#FFFFFF)
- `--muted` → light gray (#F0F0F0)
- `--destructive` → APCOM danger (#D9534F)
- `--border` / `--input` → mid gray (#E0E0E0)
- `--ring` → APCOM green (focus rings)

Dark mode (`.dark`) maps:
- `--background` → APCOM dark (#222222)
- `--foreground` → near-white (#F0F0F0)
- `--border` → #3A3A3A
- Primary, ring, destructive stay the same

---

## 9. CHECKLIST — BEFORE GENERATING ANY UI

Before writing any component, page, or layout, verify:

- [ ] Using CSS variables (or Tailwind tokens) — no raw hex values
- [ ] Font is DM Sans — loaded via next/font/google
- [ ] Primary CTA buttons are green (`--apcom-green` / `bg-primary`)
- [ ] Body text is charcoal (#333333), NOT black
- [ ] Cards have 12px radius, 1px light-gray border, hover lift
- [ ] Inputs focus with green border + green glow
- [ ] Dark sections use `--apcom-dark` (#222222)
- [ ] Spacing uses the design token scale — no arbitrary values
- [ ] Transitions are 0.2s ease
- [ ] No pure black (#000000) anywhere
- [ ] Typography follows the type scale table above
